<seg id=1> Ding Hao Becomes the First Disabled College Student Brought Up in an Orphanage in China </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Hangzhou, Sept. 1. (Reporter Zhu Guoxian, Guan Zhehui) the disabled student Ding Hao who was an orphan after birth and has grown up in the Hangzhou Children's Welfare House received the admission notice of Hangzhou University yesterday and became one of the students in the Philosophy and social science department of this university. </seg>
<seg id=3> It is known that the 19-year-old Ding Hao is the first disabled orphan college student which has been adopted and brought up by the welfare house since 1949. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "When I received the admission notice, I really wanted to jump up with joy," Ding Hao said, but he could not express his excitement by "jumping". </seg>
<seg id=5> At the age of three, he had a high fever, which caused him to have the serious sequelae of infantile of paralysis, in that year, he was adopted by the welfare house. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Ding Hao finished his primary education in the Children's Welfare House, after that, he entered a middle school in a nearby village. </seg>
<seg id=7> At the beginning, the teachers in the welfare house escorted him to the school. After Junior Grade 2, he boarded in the school and returned to the welfare house every saturday. He had never been absent in spite of bad weathers. </seg>
<seg id=8> This year, he took part in the entrance examination to the college and was accepted by Hangzhou University with qualified scores. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Ding Hao's success embodies the painstaking care from people of all walks of life. </seg>
<seg id=10> The Children's Welfare House has always been taking good care of and loved him. Since last year, They spent more than 3,000 yuan in merely paying for the tuition, buying studying materials and nurturing food for him. </seg>
<seg id=11> People from all walks of life also lend a hand to him. </seg>
<seg id=12> Knowing that Ding Hao is qualified to go to college, Hangzhou Changlong Cereals & Oil Trade Company donated 10,000 yuan to aid him financially in the university. An artificial limbs factory  donated him a wheelchair, a walking stick, etc.. </seg>
</p>
